To peel the tomatoes: To peel the tomatoes: Bring a large pot of water to a boil. Wash and core the tomatoes, then cut an X in the bottom of each so the skins loosen as they cook. Plunge the tomatoes into the boiling water for about 30 seconds. They’re ready to come out when the skins start to shrink split, and wrinkle; don’t leave them in too long, or the tomatoes will start to cook. You’ll probably have to do these in batches to avoid overcooking. Remove the tomatoes with a spider or strainer and immediately plunge them into a large bowl of ice water to stop the cooking process. 4. Once the tomatoes have cooled down, pull the skins off with your fingers. To prepare the sauce: To prepare the sauce: